IRS e-News for Small Businesses

Issue 2007-18

May 23, 2007

In this Issue:
1. Reporting Capital Gains
2. Register for Free FBAR Phone Forum on June 20
3. Time to Get Prepared for Hurricane Season
4. Treasury and IRS Invite Recommendations for 2007-2008 Guidance Priority List

1. Reporting Capital Gains

IRS Fact Sheet-2007-19, http://www.irs.gov/newsroom/article/0,,id=170634,00.html  the twelfth in a series, provides information regarding many aspects of capital gains reporting:
--Understanding Basis
--Schedule D
--Home
--Property outside U.S.
--Installment Sales
--Investment Transactions
--Gains from the Sale of Business Property
--Capital Gains Distributions

Incorrect reporting of capital gains accounts for part of an estimated $345 billion per year in unpaid taxes, according to Internal Revenue Service estimates.

Related Link:
The Tax Gap http://www.irs.gov/newsroom/article/0,,id=158619,00.html

2. Register for Free FBAR Phone Forum on June 20

If you have foreign financial accounts, you may be required to file TD F 90-22.1, Report of Foreign Bank and Financial Accounts (FBAR). http://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-pdf/f90221.pdf  To find out more on FBAR reporting requirements and how it works, attend one of three free FBAR phone forums on June 20.
  
Register online by June 17 at the AT&T Teleconference Services Web site. https://www.attevent.com/rsvpreg.asp More details regarding the forums including times, registration, and access codes can be found on IRS.gov under Nationwide Phone Forums. http://www.irs.gov/businesses/small/article/0,,id=158856,00.html

3. Time to Get Prepared for Hurricane Season

The goal of 2007 Hurricane Preparedness Week, May 20-27 http://www.irs.gov/businesses/small/article/0,,id=170663,00.html , is to inform businesses about hurricane hazards, and to educate them about actions to save lives at work, home, on the road, or on the water. 
 
Related Links:
--National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration’s Hurricane Preparedness Web site http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/HAW2/english/intro.shtml 
--SSA/IRS Reporter Fall 2006 Issue http://www.irs.gov/businesses/small/article/0,,id=109886,00.html 


4. Treasury and IRS Invite Recommendations for 2007-2008 Guidance Priority List

The Department of Treasury and Internal Revenue Service invite public comments or recommendations for the 2007-2008 Guidance Priority List. 

Treasury's Office of Tax Policy and IRS use the Guidance Priority List to identify and prioritize tax issues that should be addressed through regulations, revenue rulings, revenue procedures, notices, and other published administrative guidance.

Information for submitting recommendations by May 31 is included in Notice 2007-41. http://www.irs.gov/pub/irs-drop/n-07-41.pdf 

